    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-03-09T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-03-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="896"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d896">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 417.00/40.</note>
                <head>[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-03-09">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 9, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Nicaraguan Government has agreed to the Department’s proposed constitution of
                    the commission as per telegram of February 27. The President intends to
                    establish the commission at once, by decree; but opinion is expressed here that
                    under the Zelaya constitution he can not do so without the ratification of the
                    Assembly, which it seems will be impossible to secure.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Northcott</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
